        <h3>General</h3>
        <p><b>What is G6 quiz?</b></p>
        <p>G6 quiz is a professional and easy-to-use online assessment tool that allows lecturers and students to create and answer the assessment easily within a few minutes.</p>
        <p>The environment is safe and the assessments are published by authenticated, logged in lecturers who spend years in their life instructing the students.</p>

        <p><b>What benefits can I earn by using G6 quiz?</b></p>
        <p>For student, you can track your progress and understanding on a certain topic and hence improce yourself in that particular area.Lecturers may also provide guidance for students who may require assistance.</p>
        <p>For lecturer, you can create an online assessment to know how well the students understand the topics and which parts are the students weaknesses and need to explain more. Thus, it increase the efficiency of teaching process.</p>

        <p><b>What are the differences between Lecturer account and Student account?</b></p>
        <p>Students are only allowed to answer to the public assessment or the private assessment that is assigned to them while lecturer can create assessment and publish publicly or assign privately.</p>

        <hr />

        <h3>Create</h3>
        <p><b>How do I create assessment?</b></p>
        <p>First, you need to make sure you are logged into a lecturer account. Then, you can click 'Create an Assessment' on the dropdown menu on the top navigation bar, 'Assessment' option.</p>
        <p>Next, you will be prompt to enter the assessment details and also allowed to add question and answers to the assessment question.</p>
        <p>Once you are finished, you can choose to share it with the link or assign to private students only.</p>

        <hr />

        <h3>Result</h3>
        <p><b>Can I view my previous results?</b></p>
        <p>Yes. You can view the history of your results together with the details on your student profile page.</p>

        <p><b>When will I know my results?</b></p>
        <p>For multiple choice questions assessment, you can know you results right after you finish the assessment.</p>
        <p>However, for essay or written questions assessment, you will have to wait for the lecturer to mark for your assessment. An email will be sent to your email address once the marking is done.</p>
